Package: MouseTools
Title: Tools for Cleaning, Analyzing, and Visualizing Clinical Trial Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Will", "Smith", , "wsmith@college.harvard.edu", role = "cre")
Description: The MouseTools package provides a suite of tools for efficiently cleaning, analyzing, and visualizing clinical trial datasets. It simplifies data wrangling tasks such as standardizing inconsistent date formats, detecting numeric outliers, and handling mixed-unit measurements, ensuring data consistency and accuracy. The package also includes functions for generating summary tables and visualizing trends, making it a versatile tool for researchers and data analysts working with complex datasets. Originally developed for mouse vaccine trials, MouseTools is adaptable to a wide range of applications across different domains.
